    <p> Hello folks <br> Today I would only like to report on my 36 hour flight to New Zealand. </p>
    <p> On the way to Hamburg Airport, we unfortunately stuck a little in the traffic jam, which makes me a little worried. But it was not so bad and we still had 30 minutes before I had to go through the security check. </p>
    <p> The flight from Hamburg to London was lucky as planned and we even arrived a few minutes earlier. The change in London was pretty much the only moment in front of I had a bamel change because it takes a very long time. I can only say one change to Terminal 3 is less stress and less to do than in Terminal 1. It was just another security check and that was it. </p>
    <p> After a short waiting time we were allowed to get in the A380 and off we went to Singapore. So I can confirm that this Airbus is a good bit quieter than the smaller models and a good bit of gentle at the start and landing. The 2.5 cm more seat can be seen like the wider corridors. </p>
    <p> The service at Qantas is really good. When getting in, pillows, blankets, sleep mask and teeth were already available. After the departure, everyone got a menu with a time process, which I personally found very good, because you could roughly set yourself up when/what to feed. Since there are several self -service bars in the A380, drinks and snacks were also provided. </p>
    <p> When we arrived in Singapore, we all had to get out. However, since we were allowed to get out directly into the transit area, I took my legs in my hand and ran from Terminal 1 to Terminal 3 to buy the usual T-shirt in Hard Rock Caf&eacute;. On the way back to the gate, I quickly got into an Apple shop to get the Camera Connection Set for the iPad. </p>
  </div>
